AUDIENCE: And second,
a question from Iowa,

00:35:40.250 --> 00:35:43.951
what's the weirdest way you've
seen someone discover a trick?

00:35:43.951 --> 00:35:45.200
ERIC KOZIEL: The weirdest way?

00:35:45.200 --> 00:35:46.430
Oh, man.

00:35:46.430 --> 00:35:52.430
So there's a particular
game called "Dragon View"

00:35:52.430 --> 00:35:53.720
on Super Nintendo.

00:35:53.720 --> 00:35:56.992
And this game-- oh, my.

00:35:56.992 --> 00:35:59.450
A friend of mine was working
on the speedrun for this game.

00:35:59.450 --> 00:36:03.440
And at a particular
part, we discovered a bug

00:36:03.440 --> 00:36:04.880
that had not prior been known.

00:36:04.880 --> 00:36:06.290
And the only way that
you execute this bug

00:36:06.290 --> 00:36:07.831
is simply that you
haven't turned off

00:36:07.831 --> 00:36:10.430
the game after completing
a certain story element.

00:36:10.430 --> 00:36:12.138
And then you reach
another story element.

00:36:12.138 --> 00:36:14.560
You were expected to take a
break somewhere in the middle.

00:36:14.560 --> 00:36:16.310
And you never would
have seen this happen.

00:36:16.310 --> 00:36:18.650
But they left some
dirty memory somewhere.

00:36:18.650 --> 00:36:22.651
And what actually ends
up happening is a huge--

00:36:22.651 --> 00:36:23.150
oh, my.

00:36:23.150 --> 00:36:25.100
It's a very scary bug.

00:36:25.100 --> 00:36:28.035
Basically, it allows you to
overwrite the entire memory

00:36:28.035 --> 00:36:28.535
contents.

00:36:28.535 --> 00:36:32.585
It even tries to start
fiddling with ROM.

00:36:32.585 --> 00:36:34.294
It does a lot of very
interesting things.

00:36:34.294 --> 00:36:36.210
But this was discovered
completely by accident

00:36:36.210 --> 00:36:38.540
simply because they were
trying to go through the game

00:36:38.540 --> 00:36:39.680
all in one sitting.

00:36:39.680 --> 00:36:41.750
And it actually
turns out that if you

00:36:41.750 --> 00:36:47.750
get the exact magic conditions,
you can make this warp you

00:36:47.750 --> 00:36:50.900
into the ending credits
so that you effectively

00:36:50.900 --> 00:36:53.630
have a choice between-- if
you try to play it completely

00:36:53.630 --> 00:36:57.290
like this, you either
completely crash the game

00:36:57.290 --> 00:36:58.860
or you make it to the end.

00:36:58.860 --> 00:37:01.790
And it was just a
really interesting find.

